WEBVTT

00:00.802 --> 00:03.044
Welcome to the James River Church Podcast.

00:03.285 --> 00:07.129
You're about to hear another inspirational message from Pastor John Lindwell.

00:07.149 --> 00:09.151
Lead pastor at James River Church.

00:09.171 --> 00:13.136
It's our prayer that this message is an encouragement and blessing to your life.

00:14.657 --> 00:17.400
And I want to do a little bit like we did last week.

00:17.420 --> 00:19.943
We talked Sunday from James.

00:20.264 --> 00:26.130
I don't know that I'll do this every week, but I think there are some things that are really important for us to get a hold of.

00:27.042 --> 00:33.371
So last week, leading ourself into joy, that's so critical that we develop that in our life.

00:33.972 --> 00:52.357
And then we talked Sunday about temptation, and I wanna talk to you about the goodness of God, because when it comes to temptation, the root of temptation is the thought that somehow we know better than God, what will make us happy.

00:54.340 --> 00:55.922
And so rather than trust,

00:56.002 --> 01:12.567
him to provide the good and the perfect gifts that he would want to provide, we can have a tendency to take matters in our own hands, or we can forget about the things he's provided, and as a result, find ourselves in a place of temptation.

01:13.849 --> 01:24.786
So in James chapter 1 and verse 16, don't be deceived, my dear brothers, every good and perfect gift is from above.

01:25.826 --> 01:34.274
coming down from the Father of the heavenly lights who does not change like shifting shadows.

01:36.256 --> 01:40.700
God wants to do good in our life.

01:41.861 --> 01:46.286
I don't know whether you've settled in your heart, but God is good and He does good.

01:46.306 --> 01:54.834
And He delights in sending into our lives good and perfect gifts.

01:55.522 --> 01:58.627
Someone to give you just three thoughts about the goodness of God.

01:58.687 --> 02:02.533
Number one, we have to guard the goodness of God in our hearts.

02:03.635 --> 02:08.542
We have to constantly remind ourselves that God is good.

02:09.003 --> 02:16.575
I think that's exactly why James says in verse 16, don't be deceived, my dear brothers.

02:17.897 --> 02:23.666
Temptation comes because we believe something about God that is not true.

02:24.354 --> 02:32.946
Now, I want you to think about this because back at the beginning, the very first couple to be tempted, Adam and Eve, here's what happened in the garden.

02:32.966 --> 02:40.096
The serpent said, God knows that your eyes will be opened as soon as you eat the fruit.

02:41.417 --> 02:45.663
And you will be like God knowing both good and evil.

02:46.104 --> 02:47.366
That's a lie.

02:47.426 --> 02:50.610
And what he is implying is he is saying, listen,

02:50.786 --> 02:57.107
The reason why God doesn't want you to eat that fruit is because he's afraid you'll be like him.

02:57.167 --> 03:01.682
And he's holding something good from you.

03:02.018 --> 03:04.340
And that's why you got to look out for yourself.

03:04.661 --> 03:10.967
And that's why you're going to want to eat the fruit because God is just, he's just petty, he's just insecure.

03:11.287 --> 03:12.849
He doesn't really care about you.

03:12.889 --> 03:14.751
He only cares about himself.

03:15.071 --> 03:15.612
And you know what?

03:15.692 --> 03:18.975
You just need to do what you think is best for you.

03:18.995 --> 03:23.840
That same lie is the lie that the world is being sold today.

03:23.880 --> 03:30.226
The devil has not changed in thousands of years.

03:31.458 --> 03:32.900
You know what's interesting to me?

03:32.940 --> 03:46.294
How many Christians are susceptible to the lie that God isn't good and that he doesn't want to do good in people's lives?

03:47.536 --> 03:48.357
You think about it.

03:48.637 --> 03:50.819
How many times have you heard Christians?

03:50.879 --> 03:52.281
I'm not talking about nine Christians.

03:52.681 --> 04:00.690
I'm talking about Christians who rail against the idea that God wants to bless people and God does bless people.

04:01.922 --> 04:03.624
It's a very interesting thing.

04:03.905 --> 04:11.816
There is a whole stream in Christianity that says God isn't good.

04:11.836 --> 04:12.938
He wants us to suffer.

04:15.221 --> 04:19.387
I'm not saying suffering is not a part of life.

04:19.427 --> 04:22.932
Man is born to trouble as surely as the sparks fly upward.

04:24.474 --> 04:29.842
But I also know this, that God is a deliverer and God promises

04:30.050 --> 04:32.658
to work in our life and to do good.

04:33.538 --> 04:37.362
And when it comes to temptation, the enemy rarely starts with the sin.

04:37.422 --> 04:41.907
He starts with the story and the story is usually, God isn't good.

04:42.268 --> 04:43.609
God can't be trusted.

04:43.649 --> 04:47.474
Remember that time you asked God to do something and He didn't come through for you.

04:47.774 --> 04:48.355
So you know what?

04:48.655 --> 04:49.756
It doesn't always work.

04:50.037 --> 04:51.238
Prayer doesn't always work.

04:51.558 --> 04:53.220
God doesn't always answer prayer.

04:53.280 --> 04:56.003
He's not always gonna come through for you.

04:56.063 --> 05:01.970
And some people go so far, sometimes the enemy goes so far as to say God doesn't care at all.

05:03.554 --> 05:11.245
And we have to guard our hearts, we have to guard our minds, and we have to believe that God is a good God.

05:12.807 --> 05:26.386
And if a person doesn't start there believing for the impossible, believing God for big things, believing for miracles will be very, very difficult if you don't believe that God is a good God.

05:27.266 --> 05:28.428
settle it in your heart.

05:28.708 --> 05:30.491
He's good and he wants to do good.

05:30.831 --> 05:33.495
He'll be better to you than you'd be to yourself.

05:33.895 --> 05:35.718
God desires to work in your life.

05:35.958 --> 05:38.602
He delights to show himself powerful in your life.

05:38.882 --> 05:40.124
He delights to heal.

05:40.384 --> 05:41.726
He delights to provide.

05:41.987 --> 05:43.489
He delights to answer prayer.

05:43.769 --> 05:45.532
He delights to strengthen your marriage.

05:45.792 --> 05:47.655
He delights to strengthen your children.

05:47.915 --> 05:49.818
He delights to touch your finances.

05:50.098 --> 05:51.921
He delights to work in your life.

05:51.941 --> 05:54.264
He delights to heal your emotions.

05:54.284 --> 05:55.826
He's a good God.

05:57.666 --> 05:58.547
And he does good.

05:58.607 --> 06:00.490
It's like that song.

06:01.231 --> 06:05.578
God is good all the time and all the time.

06:05.618 --> 06:07.841
There you go.

06:08.462 --> 06:09.664
He is good.

06:09.724 --> 06:15.132
Number two, recognize the goodness of God in his gifts.

06:17.075 --> 06:27.410
I think it's very, very important for you and I to take to heart what the Psalmist says in Psalm 103, bless the Lord, O my soul, and all that is within me, bless his holy name,

06:28.194 --> 06:34.140
Bless the Lord, oh my soul, verse two, and forget not any of his benefits.

06:36.283 --> 06:44.672
One of the things that causes people to fall into temptation, Dietrich Bonhoeffer said, it's not that they hate God, it's just they forget about God.

06:46.514 --> 06:52.801
They forget not only about God, but they forget about the things that God has done in their life, the way God has provided.

06:52.861 --> 06:57.906
And so James says, James chapter one and verse 17, every good,

06:58.562 --> 07:02.327
And every perfect gift is from above.

07:03.990 --> 07:08.917
You and I don't have anything that's coming to our life that's good and perfect that God didn't give us.

07:09.998 --> 07:12.562
If you got a good job, that came from God.

07:13.684 --> 07:17.169
If you've got a good home, that came from God.

07:17.249 --> 07:20.914
If you got a good marriage, that came from God.

07:21.954 --> 07:26.041
He who finds a good wife finds a good thing and receives favor from the Lord.

07:26.061 --> 07:27.443
That's what the Bible says, right?

07:27.824 --> 07:29.346
I got a good wife.

07:29.606 --> 07:31.309
She's a gift from God, right?

07:32.591 --> 07:33.773
I got good kids.

07:34.034 --> 07:35.356
They're a gift from God.

07:35.416 --> 07:41.205
I've got grand grandchildren and they are a gift from God.

07:41.225 --> 07:48.057
I pastor a good church and you are a gift from God.

07:48.177 --> 07:48.978
You are.

07:51.714 --> 07:55.539
We've got great worship, and that's a gift from God.

07:57.121 --> 07:59.845
We've got great people leading our youth ministry.

08:00.106 --> 08:01.367
That's a gift from God.

08:01.808 --> 08:06.374
We've got great people leading our kids ministry, and that's a great gift from God.

08:06.655 --> 08:11.261
If you've got a great life group, that's a great gift from God, right?

08:12.723 --> 08:15.447
If you're on a dream team, it's a good dream team.

08:15.807 --> 08:17.590
That's a good gift from God.

08:18.211 --> 08:20.754
Every good, and every

08:20.866 --> 08:24.570
Perfect gift is from God.

08:25.030 --> 08:29.435
Nothing happens in your life apart from God.

08:31.096 --> 08:35.661
And notice he sends good and he sends what he sends is perfect.

08:36.982 --> 08:42.448
In other words, God knows not only what you need, he knows when you need it.

08:44.069 --> 08:45.030
Settle it in your heart.

08:45.131 --> 08:48.594
He is a good, good God.

08:49.154 --> 08:57.887
And the fact you've received those good and those perfect gifts is not due to luck.

08:57.907 --> 08:59.850
It's not due to your ability.

08:59.870 --> 09:04.136
If you have ability, that's a gift from God.

09:04.717 --> 09:07.682
If you add opportunity, that's a gift from God.

09:07.742 --> 09:14.372
If you were at the right time, at the right place, that perfect timing, every good and perfect gift is from God, right?

09:14.452 --> 09:18.738
You know, everything we have is from God.

09:19.938 --> 09:21.961
Got a good car, it's a gift from God.

09:23.504 --> 09:25.367
Got a loud truck, it's a gift from God.

09:29.855 --> 09:36.486
Every good and perfect gift is from God and it's God's character on display in your life.

09:38.129 --> 09:41.375
It's God showing you, you know, a lot of times people forget what God has done.

09:43.098 --> 09:45.682
And when you forget what God's done, you forget that he's good.

09:46.786 --> 09:49.009
This is why it's very, very important to maintain.

09:49.069 --> 09:56.799
If you're gonna overcome temptation, if you're gonna stay away from temptation, the first thing you gotta have is a thankful heart that remembers the goodness of God.

09:58.281 --> 09:59.622
He is a good God.

10:00.063 --> 10:05.630
His posture toward his people is always one of giving, not withholding.

10:07.412 --> 10:12.419
And would you notice his gifts, every good and perfect gift, is from above.

10:13.860 --> 10:15.122
So it all came from God.

10:16.514 --> 10:18.498
If you have it, it's because God gave it to you.

10:20.521 --> 10:25.410
And not only did it come, but would you notice it's coming down from the Father?

10:25.791 --> 10:27.374
In other words, it's present tense.

10:27.434 --> 10:33.345
So it's like God is constantly sending another gift your way.

10:33.365 --> 10:40.658
That answer, that thing you need, he knows what you need, he knows when you need it, he's sending it down.

10:42.594 --> 10:44.016
Every good and perfect gift.

10:44.036 --> 10:45.378
In fact, I would go beyond this.

10:45.679 --> 10:48.563
He not only knows what you need, but he knows what you'd like.

10:48.904 --> 10:50.686
And if it's good for you, it's coming down.

10:52.749 --> 11:01.382
How many know God goes beyond what we, I mean, God could do a lot less for a lot of us and we'd have what we need, right?

11:03.185 --> 11:05.589
But he's the God who delights in blessing us.

11:08.734 --> 11:11.698
There's nothing wrong with blessing as long as

11:11.874 --> 11:15.210
We don't get our eyes on the blessing instead of the God who blesses.

11:17.420 --> 11:20.434
Nothing wrong with having things as long as things don't have you.

11:21.986 --> 11:35.084
You gotta keep things in perspective, and a thankful heart is the key to that, and recognizing where those things came from, and that those things are gifts from God, and even though He gives them to us, we are only stewards of them.

11:35.364 --> 11:37.227
They do not belong to us.

11:37.608 --> 11:41.273
They are alone to us, and we steward those things in our life.

11:41.593 --> 11:48.082
And the proof of that is that many, the material things, especially, you don't take them with you to heaven.

11:50.562 --> 11:55.449
Now there are gifts that God gives us that are in us.

11:57.431 --> 12:06.263
And I would suggest as well, as we think about these things, don't only think of the external things, think of the internal things that God has gifted you with.

12:06.984 --> 12:08.847
If you have an ability, he gave that to you.

12:08.867 --> 12:11.490
If you have the ability to teach, he gave that to you.

12:11.771 --> 12:16.737
If you have the ability to be a craftsman, he gave that to you.

12:16.758 --> 12:20.082
If you have the ability to sell, he gave that to you.

12:21.314 --> 12:28.901
If you have the ability to counsel somebody and help somebody, he gave that to you.

12:29.982 --> 12:37.849
If science and medicine came easy to you and was interesting to you, that's a gift from God.

12:37.889 --> 12:39.611
That's not just you, that's him.

12:39.631 --> 12:42.914
He gave that to you, he gives gifts.

12:43.255 --> 12:46.578
And then along with that, there are gifts that you and I have within us.

12:46.958 --> 12:51.282
Many times we are not aware of until God calls them forth from within us.

12:52.066 --> 12:59.495
If it gives you the gift to lead, if it gives you the gift to serve, if it gives you the gift of hospitality, what an amazing gift.

13:01.457 --> 13:05.462
That's not just because your mom taught you, praise God for your mom, she was a gift.

13:07.625 --> 13:21.842
But then God put a gift in you and that's that gift to be able to host and to be hospitable and praise God for people who have that ability or the ability to encourage

13:23.490 --> 13:26.635
I mean, there are all kinds of gifts that God gives.

13:27.376 --> 13:34.567
Well, number three, rest in the goodness of God and his unchanging character.

13:36.830 --> 13:39.214
God is consistently good.

13:40.916 --> 13:45.964
He is good all the time, which means, A.W.

13:45.984 --> 13:52.914
Tozer said, the goodness of God means that he does the greatest amount of good for the greatest number of people for the longest period of time.

13:54.594 --> 14:06.820
And when we say he is good all the time and his unchanging character, theologians call that unchanging nature, his immutability, God does not change, which is a wonderful thing for us.

14:07.261 --> 14:09.586
Jesus Christ, the same yesterday,

14:09.666 --> 14:11.008
today and forever.

14:11.028 --> 14:12.170
You wanna know what Jesus is like?

14:12.210 --> 14:16.436
Read the Gospels because he's still the same Jesus today as he was then.

14:16.456 --> 14:18.279
He is still the same.

14:18.539 --> 14:19.881
He is still gentle.

14:20.121 --> 14:21.283
He is still loving.

14:21.543 --> 14:22.705
He is still kind.

14:22.966 --> 14:24.147
He is still a healer.

14:24.448 --> 14:29.715
He is still the great teacher and the great shepherd.

14:30.797 --> 14:31.899
He's the same.

14:33.521 --> 14:36.946
And the Father of Lights, when it says he is the every good and perfect gift,

14:38.018 --> 14:40.962
from above, coming down from the Father of lights.

14:41.002 --> 14:41.884
He's full of light.

14:43.005 --> 14:43.666
Isn't that awesome?

14:45.228 --> 14:47.291
Light, life, truth.

14:49.094 --> 14:55.623
And He's dependable with whom there's no variation or shadow due to change.

14:55.663 --> 14:57.927
So He doesn't change with the time of day.

14:59.349 --> 15:02.994
He doesn't say, well, you know, it's into the day I'm a little tired, so come back tomorrow.

15:05.314 --> 15:12.862
He doesn't say, well, you know, I used to do that for people, but I'm tired of doing it for people because they don't appreciate it.

15:12.882 --> 15:14.243
He doesn't, people change.

15:16.245 --> 15:27.938
I mean, your circumstances can change, your attitude can change, your opinions can change, your desires can change, your emotions can change, but God's goodness never changes.

15:28.458 --> 15:32.082
He is the same, always the same.

15:32.162 --> 15:39.151
What he said in his word is as true today as it was back then, and it will be true 100,000 years into eternity.

15:41.734 --> 15:45.799
Never gonna change, never gonna get up and find out, God's decided to change the rules.

15:47.281 --> 15:47.861
It's the same.

15:49.643 --> 15:54.670
And God has purposed that he would demonstrate his goodness to us.

15:56.212 --> 16:01.458
You know, it's interesting when Moses says,

16:01.666 --> 16:07.012
of the Lord, and I don't have it, just comes to my mind, but I think it's interesting relative to the goodness of God.

16:07.432 --> 16:10.676
When Moses says, show me your glory.

16:12.178 --> 16:30.258
Such an interesting thing to me because Moses has watched God do some incredible things, and Moses has spent 40 days on the Mount with God, and Moses and the elders of Israel have had a banquet with the living God, with the pre-incarnate Jesus Christ.

16:31.170 --> 16:32.632
I mean, he's had some encounters.

16:33.012 --> 16:40.422
He's spitting the glory of God so much that his face literally glows with the glory of God.

